review_blob: Decent pilsner - easy to ddrink but not a lot of taste or aroma. Perhaps a good summer beer.
Pours light caramel color. Smooth upfront taste with ever so slight bitter finish. Definitely not over-hopped.
beer_name: Lost Coast Indica India Pale Ale

review_blob: Nice reddish brown color with a slightly sweet bouqet. Taste does not fade but lingers with a nice slightly nutty finish. Head was little light as cold bottle beer was poured into half litre glass. Expect tap beer to have a little fresher taste and finish.
